result.execSummary:
Amil Little was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Amil Little was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 9:16 AM Prosecuting attorney Jessica E. H. Lynott in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court Reporter:  Carmen Howard. Defendant has been extradited.  BTC: Case dismissed.

9:41 AM Prosecuting attorney Jessica E. H. Lynott appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Amil Little appeared in court, in custody. Atty Greg Holdahl appears for the defendant.  DAR Court Reporter Amanda Chentnik.  The State of Illinois is requesting Extradition.  Defense is asking for a bond of $1000 cash.  Defense makes argument.  Defendant has spoken to his agent and once bond is posted here he will turn himself into the agent in order for Illinois not to have to spend the resources to extradite.  The State asks for bond to be denied.  The court has a body only warrant from Illinois.  BTC: Bond is denied.  Defendant will waive the extradition. 
State of Illinois req extradition.
Defendant does not contest.
Colloquy conducted with def re: right to hearing.
BTC:  The court finds that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly, & intelligently waives extradition.
